## Quality Gates

No change is "done" until the narrowest relevant verification passes with fresh
output. Markdown links resolve; the canonical tree stays intact.

```bash
{% if repo_type == "data" %}# define the project's data-validation gate here
git diff --check
{% else %}# run the project's test + lint gate here, e.g.:
pytest
git diff --check
{% endif %}```

## Sensitive Data Boundary

Never commit credentials, tokens, connection config, raw query output, or personal
names in tracked files. Keep tracked content host-agnostic.

## Governance

The principles above supersede convenience. Record durable decisions as MADR ADRs
in `docs/decisions/adrs/` (never renumber). Spec-driven working artifacts and all
agent/tool machinery are materialized locally per developer (git-ignored); durable
outcomes go to ADRs, `docs/`, or issues — never a committed `.ai/` or per-tool tree.

## Documentation Rules

Durable documentation records needs, decisions, and reasons — never individuals
or internal process. Keep personal names, private schedules, and absolute local
paths out of tracked files.

## Child Index

- `docs/` — durable repo documentation. See `docs/README.md`.
